channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Devastation in Gaza as Israel wages war on Hamas
item.description: The bodies of three hostages taken by Hamas have been recovered in northern Gaza, the Israeli military said. Follow for live news updates.

item.title: More than 100 people believed killed by a landslide in Papua New Guinea, Australian media report
item.description: Australian media are reporting that more than 100 people are believed to have died in a landslide that buried a village in remote Papua New Guinea

item.title: University presidents testify as US colleges see more protests
item.description: A House committee held a hearing Thursday to address antisemitism on US college campuses after a wave of pro-Palestinian protests erupted at universities across the country.

item.title: Priest bites woman's hand during altercation over Holy Communion, officials say
item.description: A priest in Florida bit a womanâ€™s hand during a physical altercation while he was administering Communion to the congregants of his church, officials said.

item.title: WATCH: Rescue workers pull woman from destroyed home after devastating tornado in Iowa
item.description: Rescue workers in Iowa helped free a woman from the basement of her destroyed home after a deadly tornado ripped through the town of Greenfield on Tuesday.

item.title: May 22, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: Spain, Norway and Ireland announced plans to formally recognize a Palestinian state, in a move that is likely to bolster the global Palestinian cause but strain relations with Israel.

item.title: Memorial Day Weekend forecast to bring severe weather, tornadoes and record highs
item.description: It has been a very active week in severe weather across the country with almost 80 reported tornadoes since Sunday.

item.title: UK PM announces general election
item.description: UK Prime Minister Rishi Sunak has called a snap general election for July 4.

item.title: The Biden administration is releasing gasoline reserves. Will it lower prices?
item.description: White House will release 1 million barrels as drivers hit the road this summer.
